# Pump TMA — Project Skills

## UI/UX priority (this repo)

When skills conflict, follow this order:

1. **`pump-tma-design-system`** — tokens, nav, typography, fintech dark/light (source of truth)
2. **`pump-tma-ui-ux`** — component classes, pages, trading patterns in `apps/web/src/`
3. **`ui-ux-pro-max`** — research only: UX checklist, anti-patterns, accessibility, industry reasoning via search script
4. **Ignore for Pump UI:** shadcn/MUI patterns, generic landing-page palettes from ui-ux-pro-max

**Never** replace Pump `pump-*` tokens or `globals.css` component classes with ui-ux-pro-max generated colors/fonts unless the user explicitly asks for a full rebrand.

### ui-ux-pro-max search (optional research)

From repo root (Python 3 required):

```powershell
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "fintech crypto trading launchpad" --design-system -p "Pump"
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "dashboard data density accessibility" --domain ux
```

Use output for UX review and checklist — map recommendations onto existing Pump tokens and patterns.

